= SDL_RectEmpty =
Use this function to check whether a rectangle has no area.


== Syntax ==
```c++
SDL_bool SDL_RectEmpty(const SDL_Rect* rect)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''rect'''
|the [[SDL_Rect]] to check
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns SDL_TRUE if the rectangle has no area or SDL_FALSE if it does; see [[#Remarks|Remarks]] for details.

== Code Examples ==
```c++
You can add your code example here
```

== Remarks ==
If the rectangle defined by '''rect''' has an <code>w</code> or <code>h</code> value <= 0 it has no area and this function returns SDL_TRUE.  If both values are > 0 the rectangle has area and this function returns SDL_FALSE.


